Elementary Parents/Families,

If you have not yet signed up for your child's School Readiness Day conference, please use the link below to sign up.
Masks will be required during the conference with 6 ft. of social distance
A student may be accompanied by 1 adult. We strongly discourage the attendance of children who are not going to their own classroom conference.
A staff member will greet you at the door, and we ask that you use hand sanitizer upon entering and someone will direct you to the assigned classroom.

*Please do not send locker accessories with your child this year.

*There will be no Open House this year.

Please click on this link to sign up for a time
https://signup.com/go/dHAmZoC

post_text:
As Medford Public Schools continue to plan and organize for the upcoming school year, it has become evident that more preparation time is needed to support the best teaching/learning opportunities this fall. With that being said, the district has made an informed decision to delay the start of the school year by one week. We will begin school on September 8th, not September 1st. Please look over the following calendar closely for all changes.

Prior to or on August 17th a message will be sent out depicting what the three learning models for Medford Public Schools will look like and include some guidelines for these models.

The calendar can also be found on the district website.
https://www.medford.k12.mn.us/page/3273

Medford Elementary Parents Association
June 8 at 7:17 PM ·

Just a reminder.... 1 week until the online ordering deadline. THANK YOU for the 22 yearbooks that have been ordered so far!

It's time... elementary yearbook preordering is now available. It's been a crazy finish to the 2020 school year.

Online ordering is the preferred method but IF you need to send in a mail order with a check for your elementary yearbook please send that to our treasurer:. Theresa Sierakowski
676 NE 36th St
Owatonna 55060

If sending a mail order please include a paper with your kiddos current grade and their current teacher as well as a phone number for any questions that may come up!

Preorder deadline is the 15th so IF you need to mail in a check please plan accordingly and do so by June 12th. We want to make sure that everyone is able to place an order if they would like an elementary yearbook.

Thanks again for supporting MEPA!!!

post_text:
Medford Elementary wants to remind you, "Don't LEGO of your Reading Skills this Summer!" Students moving on to grades 1-6 are invited to take on our Summer reading challenge! Try to read at least 20 minutes for 60 days. Each time you read, color in a LEGO brick on the calendar. Calendars can be turned in to your teacher in the Fall for a special reward!

Pick up your calendar when you return your devices to school on June 3rd,4th, or 5th.

Good Luck!

post_text: Carson Sobrack was selected as the winner of the 2020 Outstanding Choir Senior Award. Carson was chosen by his peers in the High School Concert Choir﻿ as the senior that most exemplifies the character, leadership, and skills that are expected of a Medford musician. According to his classmates, "Carson is a great leader and has an outstanding voice." He is "very dedicated to choir and his section" and "always has a smile on his face." Carson's encouragement of those around him and enthusiasm for choir had a significant impact on his ensemble this year. Congratulations, Carson!

post_text:
Today, Medford students competed in the JA Titan Business Challenge against the top teams from North Dakota, Wisconsin, and Minnesota. It was a very competitive meet with performance index scores that were incredibly high! The Medford teams performed extremely well! Yeah TIGERS!!!

Shawn and Nathan Johnson took 6th place and each won a $50 Amazon gift card

Jacob Kucera took 7th place and won a $50 Amazon gift card.

Luz Peralta, Xena Lopez-Bermudez, and Lix Gutierrez also participated and won $25 Amazon gift cards.

Great job with these students Ms. Groh and we are extremely proud of their hard work and good sportsmanship!

post_text:
As most of you are aware the Medford School District has been turning on the lights every Monday evening to represent and recognize our seniors. This past Monday as a part of this the Minnesota Association of Secondary School Principal's (MASSP) and the Minnesota State High School League (MSHSL) challenged the principal and the athletic director to run 20 - 20's. In the video you can see Mr. Babcock and Mr. Werk running this challenge. No medical attention was required. Thank you seniors, Mr. Babcock and Mr. Werk are extremely proud of you and what you have accomplished. Continue to be strong and dream big. Those dreams will come true if you believe. Do not forget to have fun on that journey and remember that kindness will guide you. Good luck to all of you.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jK5xlA9BE9j91z8cI6UPSdcDhDLOlfTB/view?usp=sharing

post_text: Since the Minnesota All-Star basketball game was cancelled, the coaches association is honoring the players through social media this week. Emma Kniefel did not get the opportunity to play but we want to celebrate her record breaking career through pictures and video. Emma holds 6 school records at Medford High School, most notably scoring 2,019 points in her career. She played 5 years on the Varsity and was a team captain for 3 years. Emma's ability to play at a very high level on offense and defense will be hard to replace. Our program has performed at an increasingly competitive level thanks to Emma and the rest of our graduating class of 2020. MN Girls Basketball All-Star Series
text: Since the Minnesota All-Star basketball game was cancelled, the coaches association is honoring the players through social media this week. Emma Kniefel did not get the opportunity to play but we want to celebrate her record breaking career through pictures and video. Emma holds 6 school records at Medford High School, most notably scoring 2,019 points in her career. She played 5 years on the Varsity and was a team captain for 3 years. Emma's ability to play at a very high level on offense and defense will be hard to replace. Our program has performed at an increasingly competitive level thanks to Emma and the rest of our graduating class of 2020. MN Girls Basketball All-Star Series

Dear MEPA,

Thank you so much for the classroom set of the book PAX. The book fit perfectly with the theme of our second unit in Literature, “Animal Allies”. You are amazing!

Sincerely,

Mrs Feldhake’s Sixth Grade
